===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[letter#Middle English|letter, lettre]]'' from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|lettre}} from {{etyl|la}} {{term|littera|lang=la||letter of the alphabet"; ''in pl.'', "epistle}} from {{etyl|ett}} from {{etyl|grc}} ''[[διφθερᾱ]]'' (diphtherā) "tablet". Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[bocstaff#Middle English|bocstaf, bookstave]]'' "letter, alphabetic symbol" (from {{ang}} ''[[bocstæf#Old English|bōcstæf]]'' "alphabetic symbol, written character"), {{enm}} ''[[bocrune#Middle English|bocrune, bocroune]]'' "letter, written character" (from {{ang}} ''[[boc#Old English|bōc]]'' "book" + ''[[run#Old English|rūn]]'' "letter, rune"), {{enm}} ''[[writrune#Middle English|writrune, writroune]]'' "letter, document" (from {{ang}} ''[[writ#Old English|writ]]'' "letter, epistle" + ''[[run#Old English|rūn]]'' "letter, rune"), {{ang}} ''[[ærendboc#Old English|ǣrendbōc]]'' "letter, message", {{ang}} ''[[ærendgewrit#Old English|ǣrendġewrit]]'' "letter, written message".

